Task 3.... Create Azure Container Registry (ACR), Pull Image, and Create a Container.

        Step1. Create Azure Container Registry:

        Step2. Push a Docker Image to ACR:

                # Tag your local Docker image with the ACR login server name:
                  (( docker tag <local_image_name> <acr_login_server>/<repository_name>:<tag> ))

                # Log in to ACR from the CLI:
                  (( az acr login --name <acr_name> ))

                # Push the image to ACR:
                  (( docker push <acr_login_server>/<repository_name>:<tag> ))

         Step3. Create a Container Instance from the ACR Image:


